\b
\c 22
\p 
\v 1 “Anyone \w who|strong="H4672"\w* steals \w an|strong="H5221"\w* ox \w or|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* sheep \w and|strong="H1818"\w* \w kills|strong="H5221"\w* \w or|strong="H4191"\w* sells \w it|strong="H5221"\w* \w must|strong="H4191"\w* pay back five oxen \w for|strong="H4191"\w* one ox \w and|strong="H1818"\w* four sheep \w for|strong="H4191"\w* one sheep.
\p 
\v 2 If \w a|strong="H3068"\w* thief \w is|strong="H8121"\w* discovered breaking \w into|strong="H5921"\w* someone's house \w and|strong="H1818"\w* \w is|strong="H8121"\w* beaten \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w death|strong="H1818"\w*, no one \w shall|strong="H1818"\w* \w be|strong="H8121"\w* guilty \w of|strong="H5921"\w* murder.
\v 3 \w But|strong="H7999"\w* if \w it|strong="H5704"\w* happens during daylight, then someone \w is|strong="H3027"\w* guilty \w of|strong="H3027"\w* murder. \w A|strong="H3068"\w* thief must \w pay|strong="H7999"\w* everything \w back|strong="H7999"\w* \w that|strong="H2416"\w*'s stolen. If \w he|strong="H5704"\w* doesn't \w have|strong="H3027"\w* anything, then \w he|strong="H5704"\w* must \w be|strong="H3027"\w* sold \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w pay|strong="H7999"\w* \w for|strong="H5704"\w* \w what|strong="H1591"\w* \w was|strong="H3027"\w* stolen.
\v 4 \w If|strong="H3588"\w* \w what|strong="H3588"\w* \w was|strong="H7704"\w* stolen \w is|strong="H7704"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* live \w animal|strong="H1165"\w* \w he|strong="H3588"\w* \w still|strong="H3588"\w* \w has|strong="H3588"\w*, whether \w it|strong="H3588"\w*'s \w an|strong="H7971"\w* ox, donkey, \w or|strong="H7704"\w* sheep, \w he|strong="H3588"\w* must \w pay|strong="H7999"\w* \w back|strong="H7999"\w* double.
\p 
\v 5 \w If|strong="H3588"\w* livestock are grazing \w in|strong="H4672"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w field|strong="H7704"\w* \w or|strong="H7704"\w* vineyard \w and|strong="H7704"\w* \w their|strong="H3588"\w* owner \w lets|strong="H3318"\w* \w them|strong="H3318"\w* stray \w so|strong="H3318"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* graze \w in|strong="H4672"\w* someone \w else|strong="H3588"\w*'s \w field|strong="H7704"\w*, \w their|strong="H3588"\w* owner must \w pay|strong="H7999"\w* compensation \w from|strong="H3318"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* best \w of|strong="H7704"\w* \w their|strong="H3588"\w* own \w fields|strong="H7704"\w* \w or|strong="H7704"\w* vineyards.
\p 
\v 6 \w If|strong="H3588"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* fire \w is|strong="H3701"\w* started \w and|strong="H3701"\w* \w it|strong="H5414"\w* \w spreads|strong="H4672"\w* \w to|strong="H5414"\w* thorn bushes \w and|strong="H3701"\w* \w then|strong="H5414"\w* burns stacked \w or|strong="H3701"\w* \w standing|strong="H7453"\w* grain, \w or|strong="H3701"\w* \w even|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* whole field, \w the|strong="H3588"\w* person \w who|strong="H8104"\w* started \w the|strong="H3588"\w* fire must \w pay|strong="H7999"\w* \w full|strong="H7999"\w* compensation.
\p 
\v 7 If someone gives \w his|strong="H7971"\w* \w neighbor|strong="H7453"\w* money \w or|strong="H3808"\w* possessions \w to|strong="H7971"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* kept safe \w and|strong="H7971"\w* \w they|strong="H3808"\w* \w are|strong="H3027"\w* stolen \w from|strong="H3027"\w* \w the|strong="H7971"\w* \w neighbor|strong="H7453"\w*'s \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, if \w the|strong="H7971"\w* \w thief|strong="H1590"\w* \w is|strong="H3027"\w* \w caught|strong="H4672"\w* \w they|strong="H3808"\w* \w must|strong="H3808"\w* pay \w back|strong="H1004"\w* double.
